<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-06-22T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-06-22T02:00:00-05:00" n="287" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d287">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/3920: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Ruddock</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-06-22T15:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">June 22,
                                        1921—3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received June 22—10:14
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>227. Following from Canton: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“June 21, 5 p.m. Hostilities have commenced between Kwangtung and
                                    Kwangsi. It is reported that Wuchow is being attacked Kwangtung
                                    troops. Ch’en Ch’iung-ming, commander-in-chief of the Kwangtung
                                    forces, is at the front”.</p></quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Ruddock</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>